This paper is about using machine learning to predict test traces, which is a software engineering task. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also involves supervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper discusses how to use the predicted traces in a troubleshooting paradigm, which is related to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions the computational resources required for tracing, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves machine learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
